summary: ANNOUNCEMENT Feline coronaviruses (FCoV) are common pathogens in domestic and wild cats in several regions of the world. they are classified in the order Nidovirales, family Coronaviridae, and genus Alphacoronavirus and are subdivided into two serotypes, FCoV 1 and FCoV 2. in domestic cats, FCoV 1 is predominant, leading to subclinical infections (4). 107 were for uncultured cross-assembly phage (crAssphage), 2 that were for RD114 retrovirus, 1 that was for feline picornavirus, and 34,140 that were undetermined by Kraken 1.0. the new FCoV-SB22 strain showed a genome of 29,137 bp, exhibiting 91.5% nucleotide identity with the strain used for reference mapping.
